3:07 PM Defendant Jordan C Newsome in court, in custody with attorney Nick Dalla Santa.  Brenda L. Yaskal appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Probation Agent Jennifer Jordan appeared. All parties appeared by Zoom. Cases called: 15CF181 & 15CF314. State argued for prison time and consecutive sentences. Right to be present recited, waived. Atty Dalla Santa argued for less prison time and a concurrent sentence. Statement by defendant. Court sentenced the defendant in 15CF181 to serve 7 years in prison, consecutive to any other sentence currently serving, 3 years initial confinement and 4 years extended supervision. 472 days credit. In 15CF314 Court sentenced the defendant to serve 4 years in prision, 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision consecutive to 15CF181. 91 days jail credit. A civil judgment will be entered for the unpaid financial obligations. Defendant is not eligible for the challenge incarceration program or the substance abuse program. 3:42 PM

11:03 am Defendant Jordan C Newsome in court, in custody with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Brenda L. Yaskal appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Cases called: 15CF181 and 15CF314.  In 15CF314 waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over. Information filed, reading waived. In 15CF181 amended information filed.  Reading waived.  Rights/Elements.  Defendant pled no contest to Ct. 1 of amended information in 15CF181 and Ct. 1 of 15CF314.  Court found guilty.  Judgment was entered.  Cts. 2 & 3 of 15CF314 dismissed but read in.  In both cases court withheld sentencing, placed defendant on probation for 5 years.  Conditions of probation are: in 15CF314 $518.00 costs, submit DNA sample.  91 days credit.  In 15CF181: $518.00 costs, submit DNA sample, register as a sex offender, complete sex offender treatment, 9 months jail, with Huber for work release.  Jail start on 12-5-15 at 7:00 pm.  13 days credit.  Bond on hand was forfeited prior to todays hearing.  Court adjourned at 11:29 am.
